{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772559811,"nonce":"hcDqG3dOcxoDqoIyTeSQr5Y4Nd0=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vfNZp","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/336","origin":"github"},"title":"ADR-0008: Follow ROS 2 official conventions by default","message":"## Problem\n\nAI agents repeatedly diverge from established ROS 2 community conventions — launch file\nnaming, licensing, and other patterns that are well-documented in official ROS 2 sources.\nIndividual issues exist for specific violations (#327 launch naming, #131 licensing), but\nthe root cause is the same: there's no umbrella decision stating \"follow ROS 2 conventions\nby default\" and no single, authoritative knowledge file that summarizes them for agents.\n\n## Proposal\n\n### 1. ADR-0008: Follow ROS 2 official conventions by default\n\nA single umbrella ADR establishing the policy:\n\n- ROS 2 community conventions are the default for this workspace\n- The workspace summary lives in `.agent/knowledge/ros2_development_patterns.md`\n- Deliberate deviations require their own ADR explaining why\n- When in doubt, match existing project code\n\n### 2. Expand `ros2_development_patterns.md`\n\nUpdate the knowledge file with explicit, unambiguous guidance on conventions agents\ncommonly get wrong. Initial set:\n\n- **Launch file naming**: `*_launch.py` (recommended by\n  [ROS 2 docs](https://docs.ros.org/en/jazzy/Tutorials/Intermediate/Launch/Launch-system.html));\n  must end in `launch.py` for `ros2 launch` autocomplete\n- **Licensing**: Apache 2.0 recommended for new packages\n  ([ROS 2 migration guide](https://docs.ros.org/en/jazzy/How-To-Guides/Migrating-from-ROS1/Migrating-Packages.html));\n  existing packages preserve their current license; always match the project's declared\n  license; include license + copyright headers in every source file\n- **Package naming**: lowercase with underscores per\n  [REP-144](https://ros.org/reps/rep-0144.html)\n- **`package.xml`**: format 3; use correct dependency tags (`\u003cdepend\u003e`, `\u003cbuild_depend\u003e`,\n  `\u003cexec_depend\u003e`, `\u003ctest_depend\u003e`)\n- **Copyright headers**: required in every source file; match the project's license\n\n### 3. Ongoing maintenance\n\nThe knowledge file is a living document. When agents are observed making a recurring\nmistake on a convention not yet covered, update the file (no new ADR needed unless\nthe workspace deliberately deviates from a ROS 2 convention).\n\n### Open questions\n\n- How do we systematically gather conventions? Scan official docs + key repos\n  (nav2, moveit2, ros2 core) as a baseline?\n- How do we track convention changes across distros? (e.g., CMake macro changes from\n  Humble → Jazzy → Kilted)\n- Should we pin conventions to our target distro (Jazzy) or track Rolling?\n\n## Related issues\n\n- #327 — Enforce ROS 2 launch file naming convention (`*_launch.py`)\n- #131 — Add guidance for ROS 2 package licensing\n- #234 — Incremental package quality improvement process\n- #265 — Add CI enforcement checks for workspace rules\n\n## References\n\n- [ROS 2 Developer Guide](https://docs.ros.org/en/rolling/The-ROS2-Project/Contributing/Developer-Guide.html)\n- [REP-144: ROS Package Naming](https://ros.org/reps/rep-0144.html)\n- [ROS 2 Launch System tutorial](https://docs.ros.org/en/jazzy/Tutorials/Intermediate/Launch/Launch-system.html)\n- [ROS 2 Migration Guide (licensing)](https://docs.ros.org/en/jazzy/How-To-Guides/Migrating-from-ROS1/Migrating-Packages.html)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}